<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 9800 MODEL - TESTING WHEEL SENSOR AND
        CIRCUITS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING WHEEL SENSOR AND CIRCUITS</title>
        <table id="t0403516" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Wheel Sensor and Circuits</title>
            <tgroup cols="6" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="s1t6" align="center"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>For sensor being checked, remove connector, (350) for rear sensor or (627) for front
                                sensor, from controller. At connector (350) or (627), measure resistance between the
                                input and output terminals for the sensor being checked.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>1500 to 2500 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to Step 3.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (350 or 627) measure resistance between the input and all other terminals
                                in the connector.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Replace the controller.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate short between circuits where resistance between terminals is less than 100K
                                ohms, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect sensor from chassis harness and measure resistance of sensor at sensor
                                pigtail connector.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>1500 to 2500 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace sensor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At sensor pigtail connector measure resistance to ground at both terminals.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Locate defect in chassis harness between connector (350) or 627) and the sensor
                                connector, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace sensor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
